items.sentence: Tom doesn't like it when people talk about him.
Tom doesn't like it when Mary sits next to him.
Tom doesn't go swimming as often as he used to.
Tom doesn't even know how to make a cup of tea.
Tom didn't tell us where he planned to do that.
Tom didn't tell me where he planned to do that.
Tom didn't tell Mary why she shouldn't do that.
Tom didn't go to Boston with Mary last weekend.
Tom didn't do that, even though he said he did.
Tom could go to the zoo with Mary next weekend.
